[49m[38;5;10m+       1[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Recipe 13.8: Python Implementation Example
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       2[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       3[0m:[38;5;10m[49m > **Heads up:** This is a deliberately simplified, illustrative implementation of the pseudocode walkthrough from Recipe 13.8. It shows one way you could translate those concepts into working Python using boto3 and the Neptune graph client. It is not production-ready. The real UMLS has millions of concepts and complex relationship semantics that this example only scratches the surface of. Think of it as a sketch that helps you understand the shape of the solution. A starting point, not a destination.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       4[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       5[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       6[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       7[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Setup
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       8[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       9[0m:[38;5;10m[49m You'll need the AWS SDK for Python and the Neptune graph client:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      10[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      11[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```bash
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      12[0m:[38;5;10m[49m pip install boto3 gremlinpython requests
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      13[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      14[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      15[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Your environment needs credentials configured (via environment variables, an instance profile, or `~/.aws/credentials`). The IAM role or user needs:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      16[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      17[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `neptune-db:*` scoped to your Neptune cluster
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      18[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `s3:GetObject` and `s3:PutObject` on your terminology buckets
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      19[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - `elasticache:Connect` for the Redis cache cluster
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      20[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      21[0m:[38;5;10m[49m You'll also need network access to your Neptune cluster endpoint (Neptune lives in a VPC, so your code must run inside that VPC or have connectivity via VPN/peering).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      22[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      23[0m:[38;5;10m[49m For the UMLS data, you need a free license from the National Library of Medicine. Register at https://uts.nlm.nih.gov/uts/ and download the Metathesaurus files.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      24[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      25[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      26[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      27[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Config and Constants
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      28[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      29[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Before we get to the steps, here's the configuration that drives the whole system. Terminology file formats, Neptune connection details, and the relationship type mappings all live here so they're easy to find and update.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      30[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      31[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      32[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import os
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      33[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import csv
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      34[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import json
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      35[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import hashlib
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      36[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import logging
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      37[0m:[38;5;10m[49m from io import StringIO
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      38[0m:[38;5;10m[49m from datetime import datetime, timezone
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      39[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      40[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import boto3
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      41[0m:[38;5;10m[49m from botocore.config import Config
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      42[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      43[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Structured logging. In production, use JSON-formatted output for
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      44[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # CloudWatch Logs Insights queries.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      45[0m:[38;5;10m[49m logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      46[0m:[38;5;10m[49m logger.setLevel(logging.INFO)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      47[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      48[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # boto3 retry configuration. Neptune and S3 can throttle under load.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      49[0m:[38;5;10m[49m BOTO3_RETRY_CONFIG = Config(retries={"max_attempts": 3, "mode": "adaptive"})
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      50[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      51[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # AWS clients
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      52[0m:[38;5;10m[49m s3_client = boto3.client("s3", config=BOTO3_RETRY_CONFIG)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      53[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      54[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Neptune connection. Neptune uses a WebSocket-based protocol for Gremlin
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      55[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # and an HTTP endpoint for openCypher. We'll use the HTTP/openCypher endpoint
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      56[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # because the query syntax is more readable for this use case.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      57[0m:[38;5;10m[49m NEPTUNE_ENDPOINT = os.environ.get(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      58[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "NEPTUNE_ENDPOINT", "your-neptune-cluster.cluster-xxxx.us-east-1.neptune.amazonaws.com"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      59[0m:[38;5;10m[49m )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      60[0m:[38;5;10m[49m NEPTUNE_PORT = int(os.environ.get("NEPTUNE_PORT", "8182"))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      61[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      62[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # S3 bucket for terminology files (raw downloads and processed load files).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      63[0m:[38;5;10m[49m TERMINOLOGY_BUCKET = os.environ.get("TERMINOLOGY_BUCKET", "my-terminology-data")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      64[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      65[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Redis cache configuration. ElastiCache endpoint for caching normalization results.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      66[0m:[38;5;10m[49m REDIS_HOST = os.environ.get("REDIS_HOST", "my-cache-cluster.xxxx.use1.cache.amazonaws.com")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      67[0m:[38;5;10m[49m REDIS_PORT = int(os.environ.get("REDIS_PORT", "6379"))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      68[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      69[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Cache TTL in seconds. 24 hours is reasonable because terminology releases
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      70[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # happen at most monthly. After a new load, you'd selectively invalidate.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      71[0m:[38;5;10m[49m CACHE_TTL_SECONDS = 86400
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      72[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      73[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Relationship type mappings. UMLS uses short codes (REL field) to describe
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      74[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # how two concepts relate. We translate these into human-readable edge labels
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      75[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # for the graph.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      76[0m:[38;5;10m[49m UMLS_REL_TO_EDGE_TYPE = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      77[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "SY": "synonym_of",         # Synonymy: same meaning
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      78[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "RO": "related_to",         # Other related: associated but not equivalent
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      79[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "RB": "broader_than",       # Broader: source is more general than target
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      80[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "RN": "narrower_than",      # Narrower: source is more specific than target
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      81[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "PAR": "parent_of",         # Hierarchical parent
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      82[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "CHD": "child_of",          # Hierarchical child
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      83[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "AQ": "allowed_qualifier",  # Qualifier relationship
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      84[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "QB": "qualified_by",       # Qualified by
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      85[0m:[38;5;10m[49m }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      86[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      87[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Terminologies we care about. UMLS contains 200+ source vocabularies,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      88[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # but for healthcare concept normalization, these are the ones that matter.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      89[0m:[38;5;10m[49m TARGET_TERMINOLOGIES = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      90[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "SNOMEDCT_US",  # SNOMED CT (US Edition)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      91[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "ICD10CM",      # ICD-10-CM (diagnosis codes)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      92[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "ICD10PCS",     # ICD-10-PCS (procedure codes)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      93[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "LNC",          # LOINC (lab observations)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      94[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "RXNORM",       # RxNorm (medications)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      95[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "CPT",          # CPT (outpatient procedures)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      96[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "HCPCS",        # HCPCS (supplies, equipment)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      97[0m:[38;5;10m[49m }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      98[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+      99[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Neptune bulk load CSV headers. These define the schema for the graph.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     100[0m:[38;5;10m[49m NODE_CSV_HEADERS = [
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     101[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "~id", "~label", "code:String", "display:String",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     102[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "terminology:String", "version:String", "status:String",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     103[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "semantic_type:String", "cui:String"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     104[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     105[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     106[0m:[38;5;10m[49m EDGE_CSV_HEADERS = [
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     107[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "~id", "~from", "~to", "~label", "relationship_type:String",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     108[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "confidence:Double", "provenance:String", "effective_date:Date"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     109[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     110[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     111[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     112[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     113[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     114[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 1: Parse UMLS Terminology Files
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     115[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     116[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this `ingest_terminology()`. UMLS distributes its data in RRF (Rich Release Format), which is pipe-delimited with specific column positions. This step parses MRCONSO.RRF (concepts) and MRREL.RRF (relationships) into structured Python objects.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     117[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     118[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     119[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def parse_umls_concepts(mrconso_path: str) -> list[dict]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     120[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     121[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Parse UMLS MRCONSO.RRF to extract concepts from our target terminologies.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     122[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     123[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     MRCONSO.RRF is the core concept file in UMLS. Each row represents one
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     124[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "atom" (a specific name for a concept in a specific source vocabulary).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     125[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Multiple atoms can share a CUI (Concept Unique Identifier), meaning
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     126[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     they represent the same clinical idea in different terminologies.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     127[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     128[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The file is pipe-delimited with these columns (among others):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     129[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       0: CUI    - Concept Unique Identifier
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     130[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       1: LAT    - Language
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     131[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       4: LUI    - Lexical Unique Identifier
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     132[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       6: ISPREF - Is preferred presentation (Y/N)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     133[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       11: SAB   - Source Abbreviation (terminology name)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     134[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       12: TTY   - Term Type (e.g., PT=Preferred Term)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     135[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       13: CODE  - Code in the source terminology
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     136[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       14: STR   - String (the display name)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     137[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       16: SUPPRESS - Suppression flag (O=obsolete, E=non-human, Y=suppressed)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     138[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     139[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     We filter to:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     140[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       - English language only (LAT = "ENG")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     141[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       - Our target terminologies only
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     142[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       - Non-suppressed atoms only
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     143[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       - Preferred terms where available (for the display name)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     144[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     145[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     146[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         mrconso_path: Local file path to MRCONSO.RRF
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     147[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     148[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     149[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         List of concept dictionaries ready for graph loading.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     150[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     151[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     concepts = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     152[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     seen = set()  # Track (terminology, code) pairs to avoid duplicates
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     153[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     154[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("Parsing MRCONSO.RRF from %s", mrconso_path)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     155[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     156[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     with open(mrconso_path, "r", encoding="utf-8") as f:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     157[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for line in f:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     158[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             fields = line.strip().split("|")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     159[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     160[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Filter: English only.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     161[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if fields[1] != "ENG":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     162[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 continue
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     163[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     164[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Filter: target terminologies only.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     165[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             terminology = fields[11]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     166[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if terminology not in TARGET_TERMINOLOGIES:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     167[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 continue
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     168[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     169[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Filter: skip suppressed/obsolete atoms.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     170[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             suppress = fields[16]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     171[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if suppress in ("O", "E", "Y"):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     172[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 continue
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     173[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     174[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             cui = fields[0]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     175[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             code = fields[13]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     176[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             display = fields[14]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     177[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             term_type = fields[12]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     178[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     179[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Deduplicate: keep only one entry per (terminology, code).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     180[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Prefer the Preferred Term (PT) for the display name.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     181[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             dedup_key = (terminology, code)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     182[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if dedup_key in seen:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     183[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 continue
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     184[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     185[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Only take preferred terms or, if none available, any term.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     186[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # PT = Preferred Term in most vocabularies.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     187[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if term_type not in ("PT", "PF", "SY"):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     188[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 continue
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     189[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     190[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             seen.add(dedup_key)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     191[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             concepts.append({
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     192[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "cui": cui,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     193[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "code": code,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     194[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "display": display,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     195[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "terminology": terminology,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     196[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "status": "active",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     197[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             })
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     198[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     199[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("Parsed %d concepts from %d target terminologies",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     200[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 len(concepts), len(TARGET_TERMINOLOGIES))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     201[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return concepts
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     202[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     203[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     204[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def parse_umls_relationships(mrrel_path: str, valid_cuis: set) -> list[dict]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     205[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     206[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Parse UMLS MRREL.RRF to extract relationships between concepts.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     207[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     208[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     MRREL.RRF contains relationships between concepts. Each row describes
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     209[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     a directed relationship from one concept to another.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     210[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     211[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Key columns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     212[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       0: CUI1   - Source concept CUI
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     213[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       2: REL    - Relationship type (SY, RO, RB, RN, PAR, CHD, etc.)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     214[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       3: RELA   - Relationship attribute (more specific type)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     215[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       4: CUI2   - Target concept CUI
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     216[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       7: SAB    - Source of the relationship
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     217[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       10: SUPPRESS - Suppression flag
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     218[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     219[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     We filter to:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     220[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       - Relationships where both CUIs are in our concept set
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     221[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       - Non-suppressed relationships
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     222[0m:[38;5;10m[49m       - Relationship types we care about
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     223[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     224[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     225[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         mrrel_path: Local file path to MRREL.RRF
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     226[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         valid_cuis: Set of CUIs that exist in our concept set (from parse_umls_concepts)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     227[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     228[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     229[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         List of relationship dictionaries ready for graph loading.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     230[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     231[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     relationships = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     232[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     233[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("Parsing MRREL.RRF from %s", mrrel_path)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     234[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     235[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     with open(mrrel_path, "r", encoding="utf-8") as f:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     236[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for line in f:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     237[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             fields = line.strip().split("|")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     238[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     239[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             cui1 = fields[0]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     240[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             rel = fields[2]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     241[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             cui2 = fields[4]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     242[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             source = fields[7]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     243[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             suppress = fields[10] if len(fields) > 10 else ""
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     244[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     245[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Skip suppressed relationships.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     246[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if suppress in ("O", "Y"):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     247[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 continue
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     248[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     249[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Skip if either concept isn't in our set.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     250[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if cui1 not in valid_cuis or cui2 not in valid_cuis:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     251[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 continue
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     252[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     253[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Skip relationship types we don't map.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     254[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if rel not in UMLS_REL_TO_EDGE_TYPE:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     255[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 continue
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     256[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     257[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             # Skip self-referential relationships.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     258[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             if cui1 == cui2:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     259[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 continue
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     260[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     261[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             relationships.append({
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     262[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "source_cui": cui1,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     263[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "target_cui": cui2,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     264[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "relationship_type": UMLS_REL_TO_EDGE_TYPE[rel],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     265[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 "provenance": f"UMLS_{source}",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     266[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             })
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     267[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     268[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("Parsed %d relationships", len(relationships))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     269[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return relationships
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     270[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     271[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     272[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     273[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     274[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 2: Build Neptune Bulk Load Files
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     275[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     276[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this `build_graph_load_files()`. Neptune's bulk loader reads CSV files from S3 with specific header conventions. The `~id`, `~from`, `~to`, and `~label` columns are reserved by Neptune for node IDs, edge endpoints, and labels.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     277[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     278[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     279[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def generate_node_id(terminology: str, code: str) -> str:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     280[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     281[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Generate a deterministic, unique node ID from terminology and code.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     282[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     283[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     We use a hash to keep IDs short and consistent. The same terminology + code
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     284[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     always produces the same ID, which makes loads idempotent: reloading the
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     285[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     same data doesn't create duplicate nodes.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     286[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     287[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     raw = f"{terminology}:{code}"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     288[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return hashlib.sha256(raw.encode()).hexdigest()[:16]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     289[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     290[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     291[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def generate_edge_id(from_id: str, to_id: str, rel_type: str) -> str:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     292[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     293[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Generate a deterministic edge ID from source, target, and relationship type.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     294[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Same logic as node IDs: idempotent and collision-resistant.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     295[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     296[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     raw = f"{from_id}->{to_id}:{rel_type}"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     297[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return hashlib.sha256(raw.encode()).hexdigest()[:16]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     298[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     299[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     300[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def build_node_csv(concepts: list[dict], version: str) -> str:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     301[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     302[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Build the Neptune bulk load CSV for concept nodes.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     303[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     304[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Each concept becomes one row. The ~id column is the deterministic hash,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     305[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     ~label is always "Concept" (our node type), and the remaining columns
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     306[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     are properties stored on the node.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     307[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     308[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     309[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         concepts: List of concept dicts from parse_umls_concepts()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     310[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         version: The UMLS release version (e.g., "2025AB")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     311[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     312[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     313[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         CSV content as a string, ready to upload to S3.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     314[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     315[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     output = StringIO()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     316[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     writer = csv.writer(output)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     317[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     writer.writerow(NODE_CSV_HEADERS)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     318[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     319[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for concept in concepts:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     320[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         node_id = generate_node_id(concept["terminology"], concept["code"])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     321[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         writer.writerow([
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     322[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             node_id,                    # ~id
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     323[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "Concept",                  # ~label
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     324[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             concept["code"],            # code:String
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     325[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             concept["display"],         # display:String
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     326[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             concept["terminology"],     # terminology:String
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     327[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             version,                    # version:String
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     328[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             concept["status"],          # status:String
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     329[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "",                         # semantic_type:String (populated separately from MRSTY)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     330[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             concept["cui"],             # cui:String
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     331[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         ])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     332[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     333[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return output.getvalue()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     334[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     335[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     336[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def build_edge_csv(concepts: list[dict], relationships: list[dict]) -> str:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     337[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     338[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Build the Neptune bulk load CSV for relationship edges.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     339[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     340[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This creates two types of edges:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     341[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     1. Cross-terminology equivalence edges (concepts sharing a CUI)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     342[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     2. Explicit UMLS relationships (from MRREL.RRF)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     343[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     344[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The cross-terminology links are the heart of normalization: they connect
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     345[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     the same clinical idea across different coding systems.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     346[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     347[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     348[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         concepts: List of concept dicts (need CUI to group by)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     349[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         relationships: List of relationship dicts from parse_umls_relationships()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     350[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     351[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     352[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         CSV content as a string, ready to upload to S3.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     353[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     354[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     output = StringIO()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     355[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     writer = csv.writer(output)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     356[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     writer.writerow(EDGE_CSV_HEADERS)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     357[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     358[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     today = datetime.now(timezone.utc).strftime("%Y-%m-%d")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     359[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     360[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # First: create cross-terminology equivalence edges.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     361[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Group concepts by CUI. Concepts sharing a CUI represent the same
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     362[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # clinical meaning in different terminologies.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     363[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     cui_groups = {}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     364[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for concept in concepts:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     365[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         cui = concept["cui"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     366[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if cui not in cui_groups:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     367[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             cui_groups[cui] = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     368[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         cui_groups[cui].append(concept)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     369[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     370[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     edge_count = 0
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     371[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for cui, group in cui_groups.items():
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     372[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # For each pair of concepts in different terminologies sharing this CUI,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     373[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # create a bidirectional equivalence edge.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     374[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for i, concept_a in enumerate(group):
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     375[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             for concept_b in group[i + 1:]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     376[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 if concept_a["terminology"] == concept_b["terminology"]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     377[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     continue  # Same terminology, skip (intra-terminology handled separately)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     378[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     379[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 from_id = generate_node_id(concept_a["terminology"], concept_a["code"])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     380[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 to_id = generate_node_id(concept_b["terminology"], concept_b["code"])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     381[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 edge_id = generate_edge_id(from_id, to_id, "equivalent_to")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     382[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     383[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 writer.writerow([
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     384[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     edge_id,            # ~id
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     385[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     from_id,            # ~from
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     386[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     to_id,              # ~to
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     387[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     "equivalent_to",    # ~label
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     388[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     "equivalent_to",    # relationship_type:String
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     389[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     0.95,               # confidence:Double (CUI-based = high confidence)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     390[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     f"UMLS_CUI_{cui}",  # provenance:String
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     391[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     today,              # effective_date:Date
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     392[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 ])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     393[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 edge_count += 1
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     394[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     395[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Second: create edges from explicit UMLS relationships.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     396[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # These capture hierarchical and associative relationships.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     397[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # We need a CUI-to-node-id lookup for this.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     398[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     cui_to_nodes = {}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     399[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for concept in concepts:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     400[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         cui = concept["cui"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     401[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if cui not in cui_to_nodes:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     402[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             cui_to_nodes[cui] = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     403[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         cui_to_nodes[cui].append(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     404[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             generate_node_id(concept["terminology"], concept["code"])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     405[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     406[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     407[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for rel in relationships:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     408[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         source_nodes = cui_to_nodes.get(rel["source_cui"], [])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     409[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         target_nodes = cui_to_nodes.get(rel["target_cui"], [])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     410[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     411[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Create edges between all node pairs for this relationship.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     412[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # In practice you might limit this to same-terminology pairs for
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     413[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # hierarchical relationships.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     414[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         for from_id in source_nodes[:1]:  # Limit to first node to avoid explosion
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     415[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             for to_id in target_nodes[:1]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     416[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 edge_id = generate_edge_id(from_id, to_id, rel["relationship_type"])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     417[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 writer.writerow([
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     418[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     edge_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     419[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     from_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     420[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     to_id,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     421[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     rel["relationship_type"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     422[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     rel["relationship_type"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     423[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     0.85,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     424[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     rel["provenance"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     425[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                     today,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     426[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 ])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     427[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 edge_count += 1
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     428[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     429[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("Built %d edges (cross-terminology + explicit relationships)", edge_count)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     430[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return output.getvalue()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     431[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     432[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     433[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def upload_load_files_to_s3(node_csv: str, edge_csv: str, version: str) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     434[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     435[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Upload the Neptune bulk load CSV files to S3.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     436[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     437[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Neptune's bulk loader reads directly from S3. The files must be in the
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     438[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     same region as the Neptune cluster.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     439[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     440[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     441[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Dict with S3 URIs for both files (needed for the bulk load API call).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     442[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     443[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     node_key = f"terminology-processed/{version}/nodes.csv"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     444[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     edge_key = f"terminology-processed/{version}/edges.csv"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     445[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     446[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     s3_client.put_object(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     447[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Bucket=TERMINOLOGY_BUCKET,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     448[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Key=node_key,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     449[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Body=node_csv.encode("utf-8"),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     450[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         ServerSideEncryption="aws:kms",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     451[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     452[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     453[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     s3_client.put_object(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     454[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Bucket=TERMINOLOGY_BUCKET,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     455[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Key=edge_key,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     456[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Body=edge_csv.encode("utf-8"),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     457[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         ServerSideEncryption="aws:kms",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     458[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     459[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     460[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("Uploaded load files to s3://%s/%s and %s",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     461[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 TERMINOLOGY_BUCKET, node_key, edge_key)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     462[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     463[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     464[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "node_s3_uri": f"s3://{TERMINOLOGY_BUCKET}/{node_key}",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     465[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "edge_s3_uri": f"s3://{TERMINOLOGY_BUCKET}/{edge_key}",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     466[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     467[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     468[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     469[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     470[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     471[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 3: Trigger Neptune Bulk Load
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     472[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     473[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode describes loading data into Neptune. The Neptune bulk loader is an HTTP API on the Neptune cluster itself. You POST a load request with the S3 URI, IAM role ARN, and format details. It runs asynchronously and you poll for completion.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     474[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     475[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     476[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import requests
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     477[0m:[38;5;10m[49m from requests_aws4auth import AWS4Auth
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     478[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     479[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Neptune's bulk loader uses IAM authentication via SigV4.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     480[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # This role must have access to both Neptune and the S3 bucket.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     481[0m:[38;5;10m[49m NEPTUNE_LOAD_ROLE_ARN = os.environ.get(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     482[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "NEPTUNE_LOAD_ROLE_ARN",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     483[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     "arn:aws:iam::123456789012:role/NeptuneLoadFromS3"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     484[0m:[38;5;10m[49m )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     485[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     486[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     487[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def get_neptune_auth():
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     488[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     489[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Create SigV4 auth for Neptune HTTP requests.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     490[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Neptune uses IAM authentication, not username/password.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     491[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     492[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     session = boto3.Session()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     493[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     credentials = session.get_credentials().get_frozen_credentials()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     494[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     region = session.region_name or "us-east-1"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     495[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     496[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return AWS4Auth(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     497[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         credentials.access_key,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     498[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         credentials.secret_key,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     499[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         region,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     500[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "neptune-db",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     501[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         session_token=credentials.token,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     502[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     503[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     504[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     505[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def start_bulk_load(s3_uri: str, load_type: str = "nodes") -> str:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     506[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     507[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Trigger Neptune's bulk loader to ingest a CSV file from S3.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     508[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     509[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The bulk loader is dramatically faster than individual insert queries
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     510[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for large datasets. A full UMLS load (millions of nodes) takes minutes
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     511[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     via bulk loader vs. hours via individual queries.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     512[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     513[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     514[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         s3_uri: S3 URI of the CSV file to load
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     515[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         load_type: "nodes" or "edges" (affects error handling expectations)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     516[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     517[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     518[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         The load ID for polling status.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     519[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     520[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     url = f"https://{NEPTUNE_ENDPOINT}:{NEPTUNE_PORT}/loader"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     521[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     522[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     payload = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     523[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "source": s3_uri,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     524[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "format": "csv",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     525[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "iamRoleArn": NEPTUNE_LOAD_ROLE_ARN,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     526[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "region": boto3.Session().region_name or "us-east-1",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     527[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "failOnError": "FALSE",  # Continue loading even if some rows fail
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     528[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "parallelism": "MEDIUM",  # Balance speed vs. cluster load
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     529[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "updateSingleCardinalityProperties": "TRUE",  # Upsert behavior for existing nodes
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     530[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     531[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     532[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     response = requests.post(url, json=payload, auth=get_neptune_auth())
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     533[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     response.raise_for_status()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     534[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     535[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     result = response.json()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     536[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     load_id = result["payload"]["loadId"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     537[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("Started Neptune bulk load: %s (source: %s)", load_id, s3_uri)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     538[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return load_id
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     539[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     540[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     541[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def check_load_status(load_id: str) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     542[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     543[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Poll the Neptune bulk loader for completion status.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     544[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     545[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns the full status response including:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     546[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - overallStatus: LOAD_COMPLETED, LOAD_IN_PROGRESS, LOAD_FAILED
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     547[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - totalRecords: how many rows were processed
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     548[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     - totalErrors: how many rows failed
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     549[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     550[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     url = f"https://{NEPTUNE_ENDPOINT}:{NEPTUNE_PORT}/loader/{load_id}"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     551[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     552[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     response = requests.get(url, auth=get_neptune_auth())
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     553[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     response.raise_for_status()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     554[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     555[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return response.json()["payload"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     556[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     557[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     558[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     559[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     560[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 4: Normalization Query Service
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     561[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     562[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this `normalize_concept()`. This is the API that consuming systems call. Given a code and terminology, it returns the canonical representation and all known cross-terminology mappings. Redis caching keeps latency low for repeated lookups.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     563[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     564[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     565[0m:[38;5;10m[49m import redis
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     566[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     567[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # Redis client for caching normalization results.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     568[0m:[38;5;10m[49m # In production, use redis-py-cluster for ElastiCache cluster mode.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     569[0m:[38;5;10m[49m redis_client = redis.Redis(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     570[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     host=REDIS_HOST,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     571[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     port=REDIS_PORT,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     572[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     decode_responses=True,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     573[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     ssl=True,  # ElastiCache encryption in transit
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     574[0m:[38;5;10m[49m )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     575[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     576[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     577[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def normalize_concept(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     578[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     code: str,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     579[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     terminology: str,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     580[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     target_terminologies: list[str] = None,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     581[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     582[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     583[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Normalize a clinical concept: find its canonical form and all cross-terminology mappings.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     584[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     585[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This is the primary API that consuming systems call. Given "E11" in ICD10CM,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     586[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     it returns the SNOMED equivalent, the UMLS CUI, and mappings to any other
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     587[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     requested terminologies.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     588[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     589[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     The function checks Redis first (most common lookups are repeated thousands
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     590[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     of times across claims and clinical data). On cache miss, it queries Neptune
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     591[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     directly.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     592[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     593[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     594[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         code: The concept code (e.g., "E11", "44054006", "2160-0")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     595[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         terminology: The source terminology (e.g., "ICD10CM", "SNOMEDCT_US", "LNC")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     596[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         target_terminologies: Which terminologies to map to. None = all available.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     597[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     598[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     599[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Dict with source concept info and list of mappings with confidence scores.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     600[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     601[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if target_terminologies is None:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     602[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         target_terminologies = list(TARGET_TERMINOLOGIES)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     603[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     604[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Build cache key. Include target terminologies so different query scopes
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     605[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # don't collide in the cache.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     606[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     targets_key = ",".join(sorted(target_terminologies))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     607[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     cache_key = f"norm:{terminology}:{code}:{targets_key}"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     608[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     609[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Check cache first.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     610[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     cached = redis_client.get(cache_key)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     611[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if cached:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     612[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         logger.info("Cache hit for %s:%s", terminology, code)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     613[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return json.loads(cached)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     614[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     615[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Cache miss. Query Neptune via openCypher.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     616[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("Cache miss for %s:%s, querying Neptune", terminology, code)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     617[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     result = query_neptune_for_mappings(code, terminology, target_terminologies)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     618[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     619[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Cache the result for future lookups.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     620[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if result["status"] == "found":
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     621[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         redis_client.setex(cache_key, CACHE_TTL_SECONDS, json.dumps(result))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     622[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     623[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return result
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     624[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     625[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     626[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def query_neptune_for_mappings(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     627[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     code: str,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     628[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     terminology: str,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     629[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     target_terminologies: list[str],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     630[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     631[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     632[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Query Neptune to find a concept and its cross-terminology mappings.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     633[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     634[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Uses openCypher (Neptune's Cypher-compatible query language) to:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     635[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     1. Find the source concept node
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     636[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     2. Traverse equivalence/mapping edges to other terminologies
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     637[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     3. Return all mappings with confidence and provenance metadata
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     638[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     639[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     640[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         code: Source concept code
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     641[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         terminology: Source terminology name
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     642[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         target_terminologies: List of target terminology names
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     643[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     644[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     645[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Structured result with source info and mappings list.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     646[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     647[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # openCypher query: find the source node and traverse one hop to
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     648[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # find all connected concepts in target terminologies.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     649[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     query = """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     650[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         MATCH (source:Concept {code: $code, terminology: $terminology})
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     651[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         OPTIONAL MATCH (source)-[r]->(target:Concept)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     652[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         WHERE target.terminology IN $targets
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     653[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         AND target.status = 'active'
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     654[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         RETURN source.code AS source_code,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     655[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                source.display AS source_display,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     656[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                source.terminology AS source_terminology,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     657[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                source.cui AS source_cui,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     658[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                source.semantic_type AS source_semantic_type,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     659[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                target.code AS target_code,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     660[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                target.display AS target_display,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     661[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                target.terminology AS target_terminology,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     662[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                type(r) AS rel_type,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     663[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                r.confidence AS confidence,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     664[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                r.provenance AS provenance
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     665[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         ORDER BY r.confidence DESC
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     666[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     667[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     668[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     params = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     669[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "code": code,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     670[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "terminology": terminology,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     671[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "targets": target_terminologies,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     672[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     673[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     674[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Execute against Neptune's openCypher endpoint.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     675[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     url = f"https://{NEPTUNE_ENDPOINT}:{NEPTUNE_PORT}/openCypher"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     676[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     response = requests.post(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     677[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         url,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     678[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         json={"query": query, "parameters": json.dumps(params)},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     679[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         auth=get_neptune_auth(),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     680[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     681[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     response.raise_for_status()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     682[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     results = response.json().get("results", [])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     683[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     684[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if not results:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     685[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return {"status": "not_found", "code": code, "terminology": terminology}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     686[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     687[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Build the response structure.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     688[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     first_row = results[0]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     689[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     source_info = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     690[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "code": first_row["source_code"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     691[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "terminology": first_row["source_terminology"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     692[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "display": first_row["source_display"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     693[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "cui": first_row["source_cui"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     694[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "semantic_type": first_row["source_semantic_type"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     695[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     696[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     697[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     mappings = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     698[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for row in results:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     699[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if row.get("target_code") is None:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     700[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             continue  # No mapping found (OPTIONAL MATCH returned null)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     701[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         mappings.append({
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     702[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "code": row["target_code"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     703[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "terminology": row["target_terminology"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     704[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "display": row["target_display"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     705[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "relationship_type": row["rel_type"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     706[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "confidence": row["confidence"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     707[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "provenance": row["provenance"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     708[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         })
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     709[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     710[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     711[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "status": "found",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     712[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "source": source_info,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     713[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "mappings": mappings,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     714[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "mapping_count": len(mappings),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     715[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "query_timestamp": datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat(),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     716[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     717[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     718[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     719[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     720[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     721[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 5: Hierarchy Traversal for Value Set Expansion
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     722[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     723[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *The pseudocode calls this `expand_value_set()`. Quality measures and CDS rules often need "all codes that represent diabetes." This requires walking the SNOMED hierarchy downward from a root concept to find all descendants, then mapping each to other terminologies.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     724[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     725[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     726[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def expand_value_set(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     727[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     root_code: str,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     728[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     terminology: str,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     729[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     max_depth: int = 5,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     730[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     include_cross_maps: bool = False,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     731[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     732[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     733[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Expand a value set by traversing the terminology hierarchy downward.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     734[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     735[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Starting from a root concept (e.g., "Diabetes mellitus" in SNOMED),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     736[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     find all descendant concepts via is-a/child-of relationships. This is
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     737[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     how quality measures work: they define a root concept and include
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     738[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     everything beneath it.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     739[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     740[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     741[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         root_code: The root concept code to expand from
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     742[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         terminology: Which terminology the root is in
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     743[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         max_depth: Maximum hierarchy depth to traverse (prevents runaway on broad concepts)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     744[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         include_cross_maps: Whether to also map each descendant to other terminologies
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     745[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     746[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     747[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Dict with the root concept, all descendants, and optionally their cross-maps.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     748[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     749[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Traverse the hierarchy downward using variable-length path matching.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     750[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # The *1..N syntax means "follow 1 to N hops of child_of edges."
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     751[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     query = f"""
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     752[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         MATCH (root:Concept {{code: $root_code, terminology: $terminology}})
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     753[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         OPTIONAL MATCH path = (descendant:Concept)-[:child_of*1..{max_depth}]->(root)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     754[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         WHERE descendant.status = 'active'
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     755[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         AND descendant.terminology = $terminology
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     756[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         RETURN root.code AS root_code,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     757[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                root.display AS root_display,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     758[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                descendant.code AS desc_code,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     759[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                descendant.display AS desc_display,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     760[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                length(path) AS depth
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     761[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         ORDER BY depth ASC
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     762[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     763[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     764[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     params = {"root_code": root_code, "terminology": terminology}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     765[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     766[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     url = f"https://{NEPTUNE_ENDPOINT}:{NEPTUNE_PORT}/openCypher"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     767[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     response = requests.post(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     768[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         url,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     769[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         json={"query": query, "parameters": json.dumps(params)},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     770[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         auth=get_neptune_auth(),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     771[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     772[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     response.raise_for_status()
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     773[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     results = response.json().get("results", [])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     774[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     775[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     if not results:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     776[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         return {"status": "not_found", "root_code": root_code}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     777[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     778[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Build the expanded value set.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     779[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     concepts = [{"code": root_code, "terminology": terminology,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     780[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                  "display": results[0]["root_display"], "depth": 0}]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     781[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     782[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for row in results:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     783[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if row.get("desc_code") is None:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     784[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             continue
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     785[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         entry = {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     786[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "code": row["desc_code"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     787[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "terminology": terminology,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     788[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "display": row["desc_display"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     789[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             "depth": row["depth"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     790[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     791[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     792[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Optionally get cross-terminology mappings for each descendant.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     793[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # Warning: this is expensive for large hierarchies. In production,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     794[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         # you'd batch these or do them lazily.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     795[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if include_cross_maps:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     796[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             cross = normalize_concept(row["desc_code"], terminology)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     797[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             entry["cross_maps"] = cross.get("mappings", [])
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     798[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     799[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         concepts.append(entry)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     800[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     801[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return {
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     802[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "status": "expanded",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     803[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "root": {"code": root_code, "terminology": terminology},
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     804[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "total_concepts": len(concepts),
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     805[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "max_depth_used": max_depth,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     806[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         "concepts": concepts,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     807[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     }
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     808[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     809[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     810[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     811[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     812[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Step 6: Batch Normalization for Pipeline Integration
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     813[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     814[0m:[38;5;10m[49m *This step isn't in the pseudocode explicitly, but it's essential for real-world use. Analytics pipelines don't normalize one concept at a time. They have thousands of codes to translate in a single batch run. This function handles that efficiently.*
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     815[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     816[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     817[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def batch_normalize(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     818[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     concepts: list[dict],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     819[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     target_terminologies: list[str] = None,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     820[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ) -> list[dict]:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     821[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     822[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Normalize a batch of concepts efficiently.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     823[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     824[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Analytics pipelines often need to translate thousands of codes at once
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     825[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     (e.g., all ICD-10 codes on yesterday's claims into SNOMED for CDS).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     826[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This function handles batching with cache-first lookups to minimize
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     827[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Neptune queries.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     828[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     829[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     830[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         concepts: List of dicts with "code" and "terminology" keys
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     831[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         target_terminologies: Which terminologies to map to
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     832[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     833[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     834[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         List of normalization results, one per input concept.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     835[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     836[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     results = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     837[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     838[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Separate cache hits from misses to batch the Neptune queries.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     839[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     cache_hits = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     840[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     cache_misses = []
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     841[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     842[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for concept in concepts:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     843[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         code = concept["code"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     844[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         terminology = concept["terminology"]
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     845[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         targets = target_terminologies or list(TARGET_TERMINOLOGIES)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     846[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         targets_key = ",".join(sorted(targets))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     847[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         cache_key = f"norm:{terminology}:{code}:{targets_key}"
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     848[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     849[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         cached = redis_client.get(cache_key)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     850[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         if cached:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     851[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             cache_hits.append(json.loads(cached))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     852[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         else:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     853[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             cache_misses.append(concept)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     854[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     855[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("Batch normalize: %d cache hits, %d cache misses",
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     856[0m:[38;5;10m[49m                 len(cache_hits), len(cache_misses))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     857[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     858[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Process cache misses individually.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     859[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # In a production system, you'd batch these into a single Neptune query
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     860[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # using UNWIND or multiple MATCH clauses to reduce round trips.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     861[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     for concept in cache_misses:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     862[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         result = normalize_concept(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     863[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             concept["code"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     864[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             concept["terminology"],
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     865[0m:[38;5;10m[49m             target_terminologies,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     866[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         )
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     867[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         results.append(result)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     868[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     869[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Combine hits and miss results in original order.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     870[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # (This simplified version just appends; production would maintain order.)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     871[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     all_results = cache_hits + results
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     872[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     873[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     logger.info("Batch normalization complete: %d results", len(all_results))
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     874[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     return all_results
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     875[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     876[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     877[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     878[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     879[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Putting It All Together
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     880[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     881[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Here's the full pipeline assembled into callable functions. The ingestion pipeline runs when new terminology releases arrive. The normalization service runs continuously, serving queries from consuming systems.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     882[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     883[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```python
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     884[0m:[38;5;10m[49m def run_terminology_ingestion(
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     885[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     mrconso_path: str,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     886[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     mrrel_path: str,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     887[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     version: str,
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     888[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ) -> dict:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     889[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     890[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Full terminology ingestion pipeline: parse UMLS files, build graph load
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     891[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     files, upload to S3, and trigger Neptune bulk load.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     892[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     893[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     This runs when a new UMLS release arrives (typically twice per year for
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     894[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     full releases, with monthly RxNorm updates).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     895[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     896[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Args:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     897[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         mrconso_path: Local path to MRCONSO.RRF
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     898[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         mrrel_path: Local path to MRREL.RRF
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     899[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         version: UMLS release version (e.g., "2025AB")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     900[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     901[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     Returns:
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     902[0m:[38;5;10m[49m         Summary of what was loaded.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     903[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     """
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     904[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print(f"=== Terminology Ingestion Pipeline (version: {version}) ===")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     905[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     906[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Step 1: Parse concepts from MRCONSO.RRF
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     907[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print("\nStep 1: Parsing UMLS concepts...")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     908[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     concepts = parse_umls_concepts(mrconso_path)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     909[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print(f"  Parsed {len(concepts)} concepts")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     910[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     911[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Collect valid CUIs for relationship filtering.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     912[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     valid_cuis = {c["cui"] for c in concepts}
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     913[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print(f"  {len(valid_cuis)} unique CUIs")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     914[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     915[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Step 1b: Parse relationships from MRREL.RRF
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     916[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print("\nStep 1b: Parsing UMLS relationships...")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     917[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     relationships = parse_umls_relationships(mrrel_path, valid_cuis)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     918[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print(f"  Parsed {len(relationships)} relationships")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     919[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     920[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Step 2: Build Neptune bulk load CSV files.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     921[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print("\nStep 2: Building Neptune load files...")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     922[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     node_csv = build_node_csv(concepts, version)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     923[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     edge_csv = build_edge_csv(concepts, relationships)
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     924[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print(f"  Node CSV: {len(node_csv)} bytes")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     925[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     print(f"  Edge CSV: {len(edge_csv)} bytes")
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     926[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     927[0m:[38;5;10m[49m     # Step 2b: Upload to S3.
